def: That which has significance; a sign; a token; a symbol.Wordsworth.In dumb significants proclaim your thoughts. Shak.
A small antenna; -- applied to the smaller pair of antennæ orfeelers of Crustacea.

Pertaining to, or containing, ethyl and sulphuric acid.Ethylsulphuric acid (Chem.), an acid sulphate of ethyl, H.C2H5.SO4,produced as a thick liquid by the action of sulphiric acid onalcohol. It appears to be the active catalytic agent in the processof etherification.

A stereotype plate or any similar reproduction of ornament, orlettering, in relief. Cliché casting, a mode of obtaining animpression from a die or woodcut, or the like, by striking itsuddenly upon metal which has been fused and is just becoming solid;also, the casting so obtained.
In a showy manner; pompously; with parade.
A European fresh-water fish (Tinca tinca, or T. vulgaris)allied to the carp. It is noted for its tenacity of life.
